        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Layer and fill",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 170°C conventional (150°C fan). Brush the tin generously with melted butter. Mix the ground almonds, walnuts, sugar, and cinnamon together. Lay a filo sheet in the tin and brush with melted butter. Repeat for 8 to 10 sheets, brushing each. Spread half the nut mixture evenly over the top. Add 5 more filo sheets, each brushed with butter. Spread the remaining nut mixture. Finish with the remaining filo sheets, brushing each including the top.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cut and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "With a very sharp knife, cut the baklava all the way through into diamond shapes: first cut parallel strips about 4 cm apart, then cut diagonally across at the same spacing. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes until deep golden.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the syrup and finish",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "While the baklava bakes, combine the sugar, water, honey, and lemon juice in a small saucepan. Bring to the boil, stirring until the sugar dissolves, then simmer for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in the rosewater. As soon as the baklava comes out of the oven, pour the hot syrup evenly over the top. Scatter with chopped pistachios. Leave at room temperature, uncovered, for at least 2 hours before serving.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
